WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.500
Enterprise core modifications are the single greatest barrier to S/4HANA upgrades.

00:07.500 --> 00:16.000
Welcome to Clean-Core.io—the automated SaaS engine designed to decouple legacy ABAP logic into modern, side-by-side cloud services on SAP BTP.

00:16.000 --> 00:25.000
Our platform enables enterprise architects to keep the SAP digital core clean while accelerating cloud transformation.

00:25.000 --> 00:35.000
Let's trace a modernization journey. We start by uploading legacy ABAP source files directly into the Technical Analytics workspace.

00:35.000 --> 00:45.000
The static analysis engine parses the legacy custom code, maps external dependencies, and highlights hard-coded workarounds.

00:45.000 --> 00:55.000
We get a clear compliance baseline showing which parts of the legacy package violate the clean-core philosophy.

00:55.000 --> 01:05.000
Next, our rule-based scoring engine separates obsolete code from active requirements, marking retired workarounds for immediate disposal.

01:05.000 --> 01:15.000
Standard capabilities are mapped to native, standard SAP cloud features, avoiding redundant development.

01:15.000 --> 01:25.000
Only the custom delta requirements are scoped and packaged for side-by-side BTP extension.

01:25.000 --> 01:35.000
Now, we navigate to the Target Architecture Blueprint. Here, we design the modern target cloud-native schema.

01:35.000 --> 01:47.000
Using secure, stateless Gemini API proxying, your legacy code structures are parsed and converted into a modular Node.js folder structure.

01:47.000 --> 02:00.000
The visual console displays generated cds schemas, TypeScript controllers, Dockerfiles, and destination manager bindings for SAP BTP.

02:00.000 --> 02:10.000
Under the Code Transformation workspace, you can review the side-by-side conversion in detail.

02:10.000 --> 02:20.000
The scroll-sync code comparison viewer maps legacy ABAP statements directly to their modern TypeScript equivalents.

02:20.000 --> 02:30.000
Architects can easily audit the refactored code patterns and ensure secure database queries and BTP SDK conventions are followed.

02:30.000 --> 02:42.000
For verification, the platform automatically mounts the new TypeScript code inside an Isolated Testing Sandbox.

02:42.000 --> 02:50.000
The system runs selective, granular unit tests, showing real-time TAP-formatted execution logs and passing assertions.

02:50.000 --> 02:57.000
Once validated, we generate the final deployable asset.

02:57.000 --> 03:07.000
Click 'Download Handover Package' to export a complete ZIP bundle with package.json configs, tests, and markdown documentation.

03:07.000 --> 03:12.000
Keep your ERP core pristine. Build fast, scale safe, and join the Clean-Core.io Pilot today.
